---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { useCaseBySlug } from '../../data/use-cases';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const uc = useCaseBySlug('loyalty')!;
const path = '/use-cases/loyalty';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'use-cases/loyalty');
const desc = description(site, 'use-cases/loyalty');

const featuredSlugs = ['sequenzy', 'marsello', 'yotpo-email-sms', 'klaviyo', 'omnisend'];
const featuredApps = featuredSlugs.map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const comparisonApps = [
  'sequenzy', 'marsello', 'yotpo-email-sms', 'klaviyo', 'omnisend', 'drip',
  'privy', 'shopify-email', 'sendlane', 'activecampaign',
].map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is the best Shopify email app for loyalty campaigns?',
    answer: 'Sequenzy ranks first for loyalty email strategy — enrollment timing, points expiration warnings, tier celebration without promo collision. Marsello wins for omnichannel POS plus Shopify loyalty tiers. Yotpo Email & SMS excels when loyalty and reviews share one suite.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should loyalty enrollment emails send?',
    answer: 'After second order or first order above AOV threshold — not to one-time discount buyers. Enrollment on second purchase signals habit forming. Premature loyalty pitch to deal-seekers wastes points liability.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should loyalty emails duplicate promotional sends?',
    answer: 'No — coordinate calendars. Loyalty tier achievement email should suppress same-day promo blast. Points expiration warning is operational, not promotional discount.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do loyalty and VIP segments differ?',
    answer: 'VIP is recognition-based on LTV and behavior; loyalty is program enrollment with points mechanics. Overlap exists — VIP may auto-qualify for top tier. See <a class="link" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP guide</a> for exclusion rules.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What loyalty enrollment rate is realistic?',
    answer: '40–70% of eligible repeat buyers enroll when email invitation is clear and second-order triggered. Lower if enrollment requires account creation friction.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can Shopify Email run loyalty campaigns?',
    answer: 'Manual broadcasts only — no points balance dynamic blocks, tier triggers, or expiration automation. Loyalty requires Marsello, Yotpo, Smile, or platform with loyalty integration.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do points expiration emails work?',
    answer: 'Warn at 30 days and 7 days before expiration with clear redemption CTA. Suppress if points already redeemed. Expiration without warning trains customers to ignore program.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should wholesale accounts get loyalty email?',
    answer: 'Usually excluded — B2B pricing conflicts with points earning. Segment wholesale in <a class="link" href="/for/b2b-wholesale">B2B guide</a> before loyalty enrollment.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should loyalty emails include product recommendations?',
    answer: 'Yes when recommendations use points redemption or earn context — "redeem 500 points on these SKUs" beats generic product grid. Avoid duplicating promotional sale grid same week. Personalize from last purchase category.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I sunset inactive loyalty members?',
    answer: 'Points expiration warnings are the primary sunset mechanism — not deleting accounts. After expiration, reduce email frequency to quarterly program updates until re-engagement or explicit unsubscribe. Wholesale and employee accounts excluded from automated expiration.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is points liability reporting?',
    answer: 'Finance tracks outstanding points as deferred revenue — email expiration campaigns affect liability schedule. Coordinate expiration email timing with finance close. Sudden mass expiration without warning creates support spike and brand damage.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can loyalty work without email platform integration?',
    answer: 'Manual CSV export of tier changes weekly is fragile — automate via Marsello, Yotpo, or loyalty app webhook to Klaviyo or Sequenzy. Delayed tier celebration email reduces perk impact; immediate send reinforces behavior.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should loyalty emails reference competitor sales?',
    answer: 'Never — loyalty is relationship maintenance, not price matching. Reference earned perks, tier progress, and exclusive access instead. Cross-link to <a class="link" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP segments</a> when top-tier members qualify for recognition beyond points.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="text-sm font-bold text-[#9a5b16] hover:text-[#24170f]">← All use cases</a>
      <p class="editorial-kicker mt-6">Loyalty</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Best Shopify email apps for loyalty campaigns</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Loyalty email is the habit reinforcement layer — points earned notifications, tier upgrades, expiration warnings, and redemption nudges that turn second-time buyers into third-time buyers without another 20% code. When loyalty emails duplicate weekend promos, you train members to ignore both. The right Shopify email app syncs points balance, tier status, and redemption deadlines into lifecycle sends with promotional collision control.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[#5d3a1d]">
        This playbook ranks apps for {uc.job}. We evaluated loyalty platform integration, enrollment timing, points expiration automation, and omnichannel tier sync for POS-plus-Shopify retailers. Loyalty email should feel like recognition, not another promotional slot in the calendar. Programs that email tier milestones without purchase context read like spam even when the subscriber has thousands of points.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Full app rankings</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP segments</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/for/food-and-beverage">Food & beverage</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Top Shopify email apps for loyalty"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Best overall', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Loyalty lifecycle playbooks — enrollment timing, expiration warnings, tier celebration, promo collision rules.' },
        { label: 'Best omnichannel', tool: 'Marsello', reason: 'POS and Shopify unified loyalty tiers with coordinated email campaigns.' },
        { label: 'Best suite', tool: 'Yotpo Email & SMS', reason: 'Loyalty points in email blocks alongside reviews and SMS when Yotpo loyalty is live.' },
        { label: 'Best data depth', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Loyalty app integrations with segment triggers on points earned and tier changed events.' },
        { label: 'Best fast setup', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Basic loyalty integration emails for SMB with Smile or similar apps.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Three loyalty email scenarios</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — Coffee roaster, replenishment plus loyalty.</strong> Sequenzy replenishment email included points balance and earn-double on reorder — 23% higher reorder rate than discount reminder for enrolled members.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — Omnichannel home retailer, Marsello tiers.</strong> POS and online purchases unified; tier upgrade email fired immediately with exclusive early access perk. Email collision rule suppressed promo same day. Repeat purchase frequency up 16%.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Beauty brand, Yotpo loyalty.</strong> Points expiration 30-day warning recovered 31% of at-risk points value. Review submission earned bonus points email drove UGC loop per <a class="link" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">reviews guide</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Execution playbook</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Loyalty operating contract</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <div><h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Trigger</h3><p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.trigger}</p></div>
        <div><h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Timing</h3><p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.timing}</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8"><h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Exclusions</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">{uc.exclusions.map((e) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{e}</li>)}</ul>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8"><h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Metrics</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">{uc.metrics.map((m) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{m}</li>)}</ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Comparison table</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">10 Shopify apps for loyalty campaigns</h2>
      <table class="mt-8 w-full min-w-[720px] text-left text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/15 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-[#9a5b16]">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">App</th><th class="py-3 pr-4">Loyalty fit</th><th class="py-3 pr-4">Pricing</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Shopify depth</th><th class="py-3 pr-4">Automation</th><th class="py-3">Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-[#4a2d17]">
          {comparisonApps.map((app, i) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/8">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-[#24170f]"><a class="link" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>{i + 1}. {app.name}</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.bestFor}</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.pricing}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.shopifyDepth}</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.automationDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3">★ {app.rating}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container space-y-12 pb-16">
    <p class="editorial-kicker">Detailed reviews</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Five apps for loyalty campaigns</h2>

    <ToolReview app={featuredApps[0]} rank={1} badge="Editor's choice" paragraphs={[
      'Sequenzy leads loyalty email because points programs fail on communication timing — not points math. Playbooks define enrollment on second order, tier celebration immediate, expiration warnings at 30 and 7 days, redemption nudges on replenishment.',
      'Promo collision suppression prevents loyalty member receiving "20% off everything" same day as tier upgrade — devalues both messages.',
      'Works alongside Marsello, Yotpo, Smile — strategy layer when loyalty app handles ledger, email platform handles orchestration.',
      'Discount-dependent one-time buyers excluded from enrollment — protects points liability and program quality.',
    ]} />

    <ToolReview app={featuredApps[1]} rank={2} paragraphs={[
      'Marsello is loyalty-native for omnichannel — POS plus Shopify tier sync, email campaigns triggered on points and tier events without brittle integrations.',
      'Retailers with showroom purchases need unified tier — online-only email platforms miss half the loyalty story.',
      'Email depth adequate for loyalty-centric ops; advanced lifecycle may add Sequenzy or Klaviyo alongside.',
      'Best when loyalty is operational hub, not email-afterthought.',
    ]} />

    <ToolReview app={featuredApps[2]} rank={3} paragraphs={[
      'Yotpo loyalty plus email plus reviews creates retention flywheel — earn points for review, redeem on replenishment email.',
      'Dynamic points balance blocks in templates — no manual merge tags each send.',
      'Modular pricing — audit cost if only using loyalty email slice of suite.',
      'Strong for beauty and consumables with habitual purchase patterns.',
    ]} />

    <ToolReview app={featuredApps[3]} rank={4} paragraphs={[
      'Klaviyo integrates Smile, LoyaltyLion, Yotpo — custom events on points earned trigger flows with full segmentation power.',
      'RFM plus loyalty tier boolean segments — Champions in top loyalty tier get different creative than Silver first-time redeemers.',
      'Integration setup required per loyalty app — flexible once connected.',
      'Scale choice when loyalty is one input into complex retention graph.',
    ]} />

    <ToolReview app={featuredApps[4]} rank={5} paragraphs={[
      'Omnisend basic loyalty integrations cover SMB — enrollment and points emails with Smile common pairing.',
      'Less tier complexity than Marsello — fine for single-tier points programs.',
      'Fast deploy for stores adding loyalty to existing Omnisend stack.',
      'Graduate when tier logic and POS sync matter.',
    ]} />
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Enrollment gate</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Who gets invited</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Second order minimum, or first order above AOV threshold with full-price component. Exclude heavy discount-only buyers. Invitation email explains earn and redeem mechanics in one screen — not legal terms PDF.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Expiration series</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Save points before they die</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        T-30 days: balance reminder with easy redeem SKUs. T-7 days: urgency without fake scarcity. Suppress if redeemed. Unredeemed expiration hurts program trust — warn responsibly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Loyalty is retention not acquisition</h2>
      <p>Do not pitch loyalty in <a class="link" href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome</a> to strangers. Earn enrollment through behavior first. Coordinate with <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount strategy</a> — points replace discounts for enrolled members where possible.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Points liability</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Finance and loyalty email alignment</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Points are deferred revenue — expiration emails affect liability accounting. Warn finance before aggressive expiration campaigns. Double-points promos need margin approval. Marsello and Yotpo report points outstanding; email cadence should not spike redemptions beyond inventory planning.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Tier downgrade communications matter as much as upgrade — silent demotion erodes trust. Email when customer approaches tier boundary with clear path to retain status.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Referral tie-in</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Loyalty members as acquisition channel</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Enrolled members with high NPS receive referral email after positive <a class="link" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">review</a> submission — warm moment for ask. Referral bonus points beat discount for referrer and referee on margin. Track referral revenue separately in <a class="link" href="/use-cases/analytics">analytics</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Quarterly loyalty email audit</h2>
      <p>Export enrolled members, points liability, redemption rate, and email frequency. Compare repeat purchase frequency enrolled versus eligible non-enrolled — if no lift, enrollment invitation or perks need rework not more email. Check collision log with <a class="link" href="/use-cases/black-friday">BFCM</a> and site-wide promos. Marsello and Yotpo dashboards plus Sequenzy or Klaviyo send logs should tell one coherent story.</p>
      <p>Tier distribution drift: too many top tier members dilutes exclusivity — tighten qualification. Too few indicates enrollment friction or weak invitation email. A/B invitation timing: post second order versus post first high-AOV order for <a class="link" href="/for/high-aov">high-AOV stores</a>.</p>
      <p>Document loyalty email decisions in same changelog as <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount policy</a> — points and codes should not stack without explicit approval.</p>
      <p>POS-only loyalty members without email need email capture at enrollment — in-store staff script for email opt-in. Marsello bridges this; email-only platforms miss half the loyalty story without POS integration.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Merchant scenario: coffee brand with invisible loyalty program</h2>
      <p>
        A $41k/month specialty coffee brand ran Marsello loyalty with 2,400 enrolled members but Klaviyo emails never referenced points balance — members did not know they earned rewards. Tier upgrade happened silently; no email on Silver to Gold transition. BFCM double points promo collided with site-wide 20% sale and cart flow 10% code — triple stack on some orders. Loyalty invitation sent day one post first purchase competing with post-purchase brew guide. Non-enrolled repeat buyers received winback 25% while enrolled members got points-only messaging — enrolled cohort actually paid more with worse perceived value. Repeat purchase frequency enrolled versus eligible non-enrolled showed zero lift — program existed on paper only.
      </p>
      <p>
        Loyalty email integration rebuild: Marsello points balance merge tag in post-purchase email two and replenishment. Tier upgrade trigger email within 24 hours with perk explanation. Invitation moved to after second order or $120 spend. BFCM collision doc — loyalty double points OR site sale depth, not both without finance approval. Enrolled segment gets early access not extra discount during peaks. Repeat purchase frequency enrolled rose 18% in two quarters; redemption rate rose from 4% to 22%; points liability tracked monthly in finance export.
      </p>
      <p>
        Barista team at two retail locations received script for email capture at enrollment — POS-only members dropped from 34% to 9% of enrolled base. Points balance visibility in email turned abstract program into tangible balance customers checked before reordering. Collision doc lived in finance shared drive; marketing could not enable double points without CFO checkbox during peak weeks.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">90-day rollout: loyalty email integration</h2>
      <p>
        Days 1–14: Audit enrollment rate, redemption rate, points liability, email mention of loyalty in any flow. Reconcile Marsello or Yotpo tier with ESP segments. Map collision with BFCM, cart, winback discount policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Days 15–30: Add points balance and tier to post-purchase and replenishment templates. Build tier upgrade and welcome-to-program emails. Move enrollment invitation to high-intent moment — second order not first.
      </p>
      <p>
        Days 31–60: Enrolled versus non-enrolled reporting in <a class="link" href="/use-cases/analytics">analytics</a>. Referral ask after positive review for high-NPS members. POS email capture script if retail exists. Collision log with site promos.
      </p>
      <p>
        Days 61–90: Quarterly audit — tier distribution, liability, frequency caps, lift versus control. Tighten top tier if diluted. Align with <a class="link" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP</a> if parallel — one customer story. Document points plus codes stacking rules with discount policy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Margin math: loyalty points versus discount stack</h2>
      <p>
        Triple stack incident: 20% sale + 10% cart + double points redemption on $85 order — effective discount 28%+ plus points liability $4.25. 140 orders during collision week × extra 8 points margin erosion ≈ $950 weekly leak. Loyalty invitation with 500 bonus points ($5 liability) at second order converts 22% enrollment versus 8% at first order — enrolled member repeat frequency +18% over 6 months: 400 members × 0.3 extra orders × $54 × 45% margin = $2,916 incremental versus $2,000 points liability issued — positive if redemption governed.
      </p>
      <p>
        Zero-lift enrolled program cost: Marsello $165/mo + operator 4 hr/mo with no repeat lift = pure cost until email integration surfaces points at decision moments — replenishment and post-purchase. Email integration build 6 hours; break-even when 15 incremental repeat orders monthly at $54.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Failure rehearsal: loyalty email failures</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Invisible points.</strong> Members never see balance; no lift. Fix: merge tag in replenishment and post-purchase.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Triple stack BFCM.</strong> Points plus sale plus cart code. Fix: collision doc; finance approval matrix.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Early invitation.</strong> Day one competes with education. Fix: invite after second order or spend threshold.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Tier conflict.</strong> VIP segment ≠ loyalty Gold; conflicting emails. Fix: nightly tier sync; unified perks story.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Enrolled worse deals.</strong> Non-enrolled get winback discount; members get nothing. Fix: enrolled early access; non-enrolled winback only.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Cross-workflow dependencies for loyalty email</h2>
      <p>
        Loyalty email must surface points balance at decision moments in post-purchase, replenishment, and browse — invisible points produce zero lift versus eligible non-enrolled cohort. Tier sync between Marsello, Yotpo, or Smile and ESP VIP segment prevents conflicting tier emails same week from <a class="link" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP playbook</a>. BFCM collision doc governs double points versus site-wide sale depth — triple stack with cart code destroys margin documented in <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount governance</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Enrollment invitation timing after second order avoids collision with welcome and post-purchase education from <a class="link" href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome</a> and post-purchase paths. Referral ask after positive review ties to <a class="link" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">reviews guide</a> warm moment timing. Points liability tracking in finance export connects loyalty to <a class="link" href="/use-cases/analytics">analytics</a> monthly — redemption rate and enrolled versus non-enrolled repeat frequency prove program ROI.         POS-only loyalty members need email capture at enrollment — Marsello bridges retail and email; email-only platforms miss half the story without integration discipline.
      </p>
      <p>
        Weekly operator rhythm: Monday enrolled versus eligible repeat frequency delta; Wednesday points liability trend; Friday BFCM collision log if peak nearby. Monthly: tier upgrade email trigger test; redemption rate by cohort. Quarterly: enrolled lift proof — if zero lift, perks or invitation timing need rework not more email.         Points balance visible in replenishment and post-purchase every send — invisible points equal invisible program.
      </p>
      <p>
        Loyalty email succeeds when points appear at reorder decision moments — not in monthly generic newsletters members never open. Track enrolled versus eligible repeat frequency monthly; zero lift for two consecutive quarters means invitation timing or perk visibility failed, not member interest. Redemption rate below ten percent signals earn mechanics too slow or burn options too unattractive — email cannot fix program design economics alone. Enrolled member email must reference tier name and next perk threshold — vague points balance without context underperforms. BFCM collision doc signed before October 1 — verbal agreement fails when sale depth changes in planning.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Merchant scenario (use-cases): Loyalty rollout checkpoint</h2>
      <p>
        Shopify operators evaluating Loyalty should document week-one baseline metrics before claiming migration wins — welcome time-to-live, cart suppression accuracy, post-purchase edge cases, and winback engagement splits scored on staff accounts. Model 12-month platform cost at projected list size including popup imports and peak-season send spikes, not current-month invoice alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        Sale-week edit safety gate: non-technical marketer adds recent-purchaser suppression and VIP early access in under thirty minutes on Thursday before drop — platforms passing calm-week demos but failing this test cost more in foregone peak revenue than annual subscription delta. Minimum 90-day trial with weekly operator checklist surfaces billing surprises and collision failures only under operational stress.
      </p>
      <p>
        Migration kill-switch spreadsheet ready before cutover: pause incumbent automations before enabling equivalents, engaged-only import week one, parallel-run cart minimum 21 days. Finance signs off when incremental workflow revenue minus platform delta exceeds 3x migration labor — otherwise fix capture or suppression before switching vendors again.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/replenishment">Replenishment →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/for/jewelry">Jewelry →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Merchant scenario: Loyalty on Shopify Plus consumables</h2>
      <p>
        CleanPour drinkware ($74k/mo) rebuilt Loyalty after collision audit found cart and winback double-discounting same week — unsubscribes spiked 0.4 points. Separated flows with documented suppression hierarchy: cart active blocks winback discount path; recent purchaser hard exclusion 14 days. Holdout 5% measures true incrementality; gross attributed revenue without holdout overstated program value 22%.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f] mt-10">90-day Loyalty implementation</h2>
      <p><strong>Days 1–30:</strong> Baseline metrics and staff-account edge-case tests — gift buyer, subscription tag, wholesale exclusion. <strong>Days 31–60:</strong> Production flow with collision matrix signed by retention lead. <strong>Days 61–90:</strong> Margin reporting with discount cost subtracted; weekly operator rhythm on calendar.</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f] mt-10">Margin math: Loyalty with discount governance</h2>
      <p>
        CleanPour tracked margin per recovered order not gross recovery revenue — 15% blanket discount on $52 AOV surrendered $7.80 margin per recovery. Graduated ladder lifted gross profit per send 34% with 8% lower gross revenue — finance approved expanded send volume on profit-positive path only.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f] mt-10">Failure rehearsal: Loyalty breaks</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Collision with cart.</strong> Two discounts same customer same week — Fix: hierarchy doc. <strong>No sunset.</strong> Perpetual automation trains ignore — Fix: three-touch series max then annual check-in. <strong>Guest data gap.</strong> ROI ceiling until checkout captures email — Fix: segment logged-in versus guest recovery separately.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Workflow test checklist for loyalty</h2>
      <p>
        Run this loyalty validation on staff accounts before peak season: (1) welcome branches correctly by signup source and suppresses existing customers; (2) cart recovery excludes recent purchasers of same SKU variant; (3) post-purchase suppresses gift buyers from discount cross-sell and respects try-on or education delay windows; (4) winback splits engaged versus unengaged and sunsets after three touches. Score each 0–10; any flow below 7 is migration or rebuild signal.
      </p>
      <p>
        Model 12-month cost at projected contact count after popup, giveaway, and influencer imports — not today's list size. Profile-based ESP pricing punishes capture-heavy verticals; pay-per-send rewards selective sending but still requires quarterly sunset of 180-day non-openers for deliverability. Stack TCO includes capture pageviews, SMS peak-week volume, and unused suite modules — finance should see one retention line item.
      </p>
      <p>
        Sale-week rehearsal non-negotiable: marketer must add VIP early-access segment and recent-purchaser suppression in under thirty minutes on Thursday before drop. Platforms that pass calm-week demos but fail sale-week edits cost more in foregone peak revenue than annual subscription delta. Document trial outcomes in writing for finance — incremental workflow revenue minus platform delta must exceed 3x migration labor or fix capture and collision before switching again.
      </p>
      <p>
        Migration timing: January–March or May–September only; never October–December ESP switch. Parallel-run welcome and cart minimum 21 days; incumbent read-only 90 days for export disputes. Kill-switch spreadsheet lists every incumbent automation pause order before enabling new platform equivalents — duplicate cart recovery during migration quarters deliverability and unsubscribes take quarters to heal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

